<section id="quikid-tagline"><h1 class="text-center">How to Install and use QuikID<sup>TM</sup></h1></section>
<section>
	<div class="container howtoinstall">
		<div class="row">
			<div class="col-md-offset-1 col-md-10">
				<h1>Installing QuikID<sup>TM</sup></h1>
				<h3>Summary: QuikID<sup>TM</sup> requires the following components</h3>
				<ol>
					<li>Bluetooth USB dongle to be inserted in your PC</li>
					<li>QuikID<sup>TM</sup> Desktop client to be downloaded to your PC and installed as <b>Admin</b></li>
					<li>QuikID<sup>TM</sup> App to be downloaded and installed to either your Android or iPhone device. For a list of supported devices, see: <a href="http://www.quikid.ca/quikid">www.quikid.ca/quikid</a></li>
				</ol>                
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="row">
			<div class="col-md-offset-1 col-md-10">
				<h3>On iPhone</h3>
				<ol>
					<li>Open the TestFlight Invitation email from iTunes on your device</li>
					<li>Download and Install TestFlight App via the App Store</li>
					<li>Download and Click on the link “open in TestFlight” and accept the terms and conditions</li>
					<li>Install QuikID<sup>TM</sup> via the TestFlight App</li>
				</ol>
				<p>Note: you only have to do this once. Next time, when there is an upgrade available, you will get a notification by email.</p>
				<div class="col-sm-4 col-md-4">
				<img src="../media/img/howto1.png" class="howto img-responsive" alt="QuikID_howto">
				</div>
				<div class="col-sm-4 col-md-4">
				<img src="../media/img/howto2.png" class="howto img-responsive" alt="QuikID_howto">
				</div>
				<div class="col-sm-4 col-md-4">
				<img src="../media/img/howto3.png" class="howto img-responsive" alt="QuikID_howto">
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="row">
			<div class="col-md-offset-1 col-md-10">
				<h3>On Android</h3>
				<ol>
					<li><a class="" href="/quikid_download">Download the Android apk file</a></li>
					<li>Sideload to your Android device via USB or open on your device via email</li>
				</ol>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="row">
			<div class="col-sm-12 col-md-offset-1 col-md-10">
				<h3>On PC</h3>
				<ol>
					<li>Insert the USB Bluetooth dongle in your PC</li>
					<li><a class="" href="/quikid_download">Download the PC installer</a><span> (version info: 4.5.0)</span></li>
					<li>Login to your PC as <b>Admin</b></li>
					<li>Run the installer, both QuikID<sup>TM</sup> and also the Bluetooth drivers are installed</li>
				</ol>
				<p>You can check the status and versions installed, by clicking on the QuikID<sup>TM</sup> Beta Logo</p>
				<div class="col-sm-12 col-md-offset-2 col-md-8">
				<img src="../media/img/howto4.png" class="howto img-responsive" alt="QuikID_howto">
				<span class="howtotext">The TCP and BLE Status should be true, the software also expires after a specific period of time</span>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="row ">
			<div class="col-md-offset-2 col-md-8 how2box">
				<div class="col-md-12">
				<h3>Notes: The QuikID<sup>TM</sup> App requires that:</h3>
				
					<div>1. Bluetooth is turned on</div>
					<div>2. Camera is enabled, to scan the QR Codes</div>
					<div>3. The App can be run in background mode</div>
				</div>
				<div class="col-md-6">
					<h3>On iPhone Select Settings</h3>
					<span>Make sure that your Settings are set-up as follows:</span>
					<ul>
						<li><b>Bluetooth Sharing</b> is enabled</li>
						<li><b>Camera</b> is enabled</li>
						<li><b>Background App</b> is enabled</li>				
					</ul>
				</div>
				<div class="col-md-6">
					<img src="../media/img/howto5.png" class="howto img-responsive" alt="QuikID_howto">
				</div>
				<div class="col-md-6">
					<h3>On Android Select Settings</h3>
					<span>When installing QuikID<sup>TM</sup>, permission/required settings should be set up so that the QuikIDService App is running in the background. </span>
				</div>
				<div class="col-md-6">
					<img src="../media/img/howto13.png" class="howto img-responsive" alt="QuikID_howto">
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="row">
			<div class="col-md-offset-1 col-md-10">
				<h1 class="how2title">Using QuikID<sup>TM</sup></h1>
				<h3>Summary: QuikID<sup>TM</sup> requires the following actions</h3>
				<ol>
					<li>The user adds their device to the QuikID<sup>TM</sup> Dashboard, to create a secure trusted relationship, effectively the device and PC are paired</li>
					<li>The user can simply adjust the range at which the device can be used to lock and conversely authenticate the user for login</li>
					<li>When in close proximity to the PC, the user just needs to enter a simple pincode or click enter to login
</li>
					<li>When outside of the set range the PC will automatically lock</li>
				</ol>                
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="row">
			<div class="col-md-offset-1 col-md-10">
				<h3>On PC</h3>
				<ol>
					<li>Launch the QuikID<sup>TM</sup> Dashboard</li>
					<li>Recommend adding the QuikID<sup>TM</sup> application as a shortcut by right clicking the application and selecting “Pin this program to taskbar”</li>
					<li>On the QuikID<sup>TM</sup> Dashboard click “Add New Device”</li>
					<li>Enter your PC user name and password, select Bluetooth by default</li>
					<li>Enter a 4 digit pincode which is optional</li>
				</ol>
				<div class="col-sm-6 col-md-6">
