		<div class="row">
			<div class="col-md-offset-1 col-md-10">
				<h3>On Mobile Device</h3>
				<ol>
					<li>Launch the QuikID<sup>TM</sup> App</li>
					<li>Click the <b>+</b> to add a new PC</li>
					<li>Open the Camera</li>
					<li>Scan the QR code on the PC, pairing should be successful</li>
				</ol>
				<div class="col-sm-6 col-md-offset-1 col-md-4">
				<img src="../media/img/howto10.png" class="howto img-responsive" alt="QuikID_howto">
				<p class="text-center">Tap the ‘+’ sign on device</p>
				</div>
				<div class="col-sm-6 col-md-offset-1 col-md-4">
				<img src="../media/img/howto11.png" class="howto img-responsive" alt="QuikID_howto">
				<p class="text-center">Scan QR on PC</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="row">
			<div class="col-md-offset-1 col-md-10">
				<h3>On PC</h3>
				<ol>
					<li><b>Manually lock</b> the PC</li>
					<li>Verify that your device can be discovered via QuikID<sup>TM</sup> and you can login/unlock your PC</li>
					<li>You can now adjust the range to set the distance which the device auto locks and is detected as being in range for login, this is a manual process of trying different values. 
</li>
				</ol>

				<div class="col-sm-12 col-md-offset-2 col-md-8">
					<img src="../media/img/howto12.png" class="howto img-responsive" alt="QuikID_howto">
					<p class="tip">Tip: There are many dynamic factors that can effect the range, these factors also change under different environmental conditions such as the number of Bluetooth devices in close proximity and also placement and location of the device, relative to other objects; which either may block or reflect the signal. </p>
				</div>
